{
  "text": "The genotype and allele frequencies of the polymorphism AUTS2 rs6943555 might differ among races. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Genotype and allele frequencies of this polymorphism in this study were not significantly different compared to that of our previous study (male : [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] On the other hand, in Polish Caucasian subjects (male: 1819, female: 2042, mean age: 45.72±14.91) the A/A genotype accounts for only 4.7% and the A allele 21%. [CITATION_6] The genotype and allele frequencies of the polymorphism AUTS2 rs6943555 in Polish Caucasian subjects show significant differences from those in the Japanese population examined in this study [genotype: χ 2 (2)=39.4, p<0.01; allele: χ 2 (1)=40.1, p<0.01]. [CITATION_7] However, because the number of subjects in this study was far fewer than that in Chojnicka's study of Polish Caucasians, [CITATION_8] such a difference in methodology will should be considered. Likewise, the age ranges of the subjects in Chojnicka's [CITATION_9] studies that have roughly the same age range was also observed. Therefore, if the different results to our study are confirmed in further studies, such differences in genotype and allele frequencies among races might be one of the reasons.",
  "correct_citation": {
